<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>or a rogue wanting a piece of cobalt armor that dropped when there is a warrior that could use, is just greed plain and simple.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well, the nature of parchments is different from other class specific loots because you do not know what spell you will get from turning in the parchment. If the casters in the group (pure pickup, mind you) want to exclude pure melee from rolling, they should at least offer up any duplicate spells resulting from the turn ins for the group to roll on (pure pickup, mind you).<br>
<br>
Some casters would use the argument that &quot;They need the duplicates for trading for other spells etc. etc.&quot; - guess what would happen if I said I needed item_x with 80hps for a slot to trade for a 100hp item, since I already had a 90hp item in that slot - I would be laughed out of the group while the druid winning the roll is busy selling it for pp to do tradeskills or whatever.<br>
<br>
I hate unregulated NBG with a passion, open rolls on everything in pickup groups is the only fair way to go. I was always a big proponent of NBG before I came to really think deeply about it, in the long run everyone will get the same amount worth of loot and can redistribute through the bazaar to get the items they really want/need. NBG really require a great morality of the people in the group, and especially pickup groups where you may not ever have met, or meet again a person - why should you help equip them, or their guilds instead of your own? What incentive would there be for a necessary class to camp a camp dropping some item which they will never get a shot at? (this is all in pickup groups, mind you - not talking about friends/guild).<br>
<br>
When all this is said, I doubt I would ever roll on a parchment unless every caster in the group said they had all their spells for that class - and I'm sure that day will come soon enough if they are all honest. <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19405 target=blank>Marshall Sscaley Iceblade</a><br><i><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net>The Companions ~ Team Headstart</a></i> <br>
